t6213.text: The economic cost is going to be unlike anything we’ve seen, the social and mental cost can’t be forgotten. Let’s get it right with proper, clear action rather than attempts at it that have to be adjusted in 24 hrs.

t6214.text: Good, clear, well communicated action needs to be done because there’s only one chance to get this right (and especially if it ends an 8+ week shutdown which based on China/Singapore patterns is the most effective action)

t6215.text: Discussions about payments for mortgages, rent etc needs to be taken into account and things need to be done right. We’re a panicked society right now and panicked moves with no plans are going to harm our most vulnerable.

t6216.text: It’s easy to talk about a shutdown (which is coming this week) but things need to be properly put in place first. Businesses need strategies beyond just work from home, definitions of essential services need to be publicly raised and schools need some time to set things up.
